description: Two people were rescued and emergency crews were attempting to rescue a third at a ski area on the Northeast’s highest mountain.

title: Drumgoole scores 17, Delaware takes down Hampton in CAA Tournament 80-50
description: Led by Gerald Drumgoole Jr.'s 17 points, the Delaware Fightin' Blue Hens defeated the Hampton Pirates 80-50 in the Coastal Athletic Association Tournament.

title: Leuchten scores 17 as UC Irvine takes down Cal State Fullerton 81-71
description: Led by Bent Leuchten's 17 points, the UC Irvine Anteaters defeated the Cal State Fullerton Titans 81-71.

title: No letdown: Murray, Jokic, Porter Jr. lead Nuggets to 142-121 rout of short-handed Utah Jazz
description: About an hour after their coach expressed concerns that the Nuggets would have an emotional letdown against Utah, Jamal Murray, Nikola Jokic and Michael Porter Jr. made sure that didn't happen.

title: Chiefs and DT Chris Jones agree to framework of 5-year deal that includes $95M in guarantees
description: A person familiar with the negotiations told The Associated Press the Kansas City Chiefs and All-Pro defensive tackle Chris Jones had agreed on the framework of a five-year deal that includes $95 million guaranteed.

title: Hannibal scores 24 points to lead LSU over Missouri 84-80, Tigers finish 0-18 in SEC
description: Trae Hannibal scored 24 points to lead five in double figures and LSU beat Missouri 84-80 on Saturday night.

title: Sunday's Time Schedule
description: Sunday’s Time Schedule

title: No. 20 BYU beats Oklahoma State to clinch 5th seed in Big 12 Tournament
description: Fousseyni Traore scored 19 points and Jaxson Robinson added 17 to lead No. 20 BYU to an 85-71 victory over Oklahoma State.

title: Johnson, Sochan lead Spurs past Warriors team without Curry, 126-113
description: Keldon Johnson had 22 points and 11 rebounds, and the San Antonio Spurs beat a Golden State Warriors team playing without Stephen Curry 126-113.

title: Darius Brown II hits winning 3-pointer to give No. 22 Utah State 87-85 win over New Mexico
description: Darius Brown II hit the winning 3-pointer with five seconds to play, Ian Martinez scored 22 points on 7-of-11 shooting, and No. 22 Utah State secured its first outright Mountain West regular-season title with an 87-85 win over New Mexico.

title: West Virginia bill letting teachers remove 'threatening' students from class heads to governor
description: A West Virginia bill that would provide a framework for public school teachers to remove kindergarten and elementary school students from the classroom for severe misbehavior is headed to the desk of Republican Gov.

title: Ethiopia's Tigray region is now peaceful, but extreme hunger afflicts its children
description: Once-lush fields lie barren. Mothers, faces etched with worry, watch helplessly as their children weaken from malnutrition. Hundreds of people have died.

title: Edwards puts up 18 as James Madison defeats Marshall 81-64 in Sun Belt Conference Tournament
description: Terrence Edwards scored 18 points to lead James Madison to an 81-64 victory against Marshall in the Sun Belt Conference Tournament.

title: Jayson Tatum, Jaylen Brown lead Celtics past Suns 117-107, snapping rare 2-game skid
description: Jayson Tatum scored 29 points, Jaylen Brown added 27 and the NBA-leading Boston Celtics beat the Phoenix Suns 117-107.

title: Pompeu scores in stoppage time, St. Louis earns 2-2 draw with Austin
description: Célio Pompeu scored in the third minute of second-half stoppage time and St. Louis City rallied for a 2-2 draw with Austin FC.

title: Duke's Kyle Filipowski denies intentionally tripping UNC's Harrison Ingram in rivalry loss
description: Duke star big man Kyle Filipowski said he didn’t intend to trip North Carolina forward Harrison Ingram during the first half of Saturday night’s rivalry game after the two got tangled as Filipowski defended a shot by Ingram.

title: Minix scores 26, Thelwell 21 as Morehead St. beats UALR 69-55 in OVC title game
description: Riley Minix scored 26 points and Drew Thelwell added 21, including 13 in the final 8-plus minutes, to help Morehead State blew a 17-point lead before the Eagles No. 1 seed Arkansas-Little Rock 69-55 in the championship game of the Ohio Valley Conference Tournament.

title: West Virginia lawmakers OK bill drawing back one of the country's strictest child vaccination laws
description: West Virginia’s GOP-controlled state Legislature has voted to allow some students who don’t attend traditional public schools to be exempt from state vaccination requirements.

title: Beekman shines on senior night as Virginia beats Georgia Tech 72-57
description: Reece Beekman finished with 21 points, nine assists and six rebounds on senior night and Virginia cruised to a 72-57 victory over Georgia Tech, closing out the Atlantic Coast Conference regular season.

title: Grand Canyon secures 68-47 win against Cal Baptist
description: Led by Tyon Grant-Foster's 19 points, the Grand Canyon Antelopes defeated the Cal Baptist Lancers 68-47.

title: Pittsburgh holds off NC State 81-73 to claim double-bye in ACC Tournament
description: Carlton Carrington scored 23 points, Blake Hinson added 21 and Pittsburgh defeated NC State 81-73 to claim fourth-place and a double-bye in the upcoming ACC Tournament.

title: Shesterkin gets 13th career shutout in 200th NHL game as Rangers down Blues 4-0
description: Igor Shesterkin made 26 saves for his 13th career shutout in his 200th career NHL game, Vincent Trocheck and Jimmy Vesey scored first-period goals and the New York Rangers defeated the St.

title: Farsi's goal late in stoppage time carries Columbus Crew past Chicago Fire 2-1
description: Mohamed Farsi’s goal off a rebound led the defending-champion Columbus Crew to a thrilling 2-1 win over Chicago and extended the Fire’s woes in central Ohio.

title: John Tavares breaks late tie with 20th goal, Maple Leafs beat Canadiens 3-2
description: John Tavares broke a tie with 6:46 left with his 20th goal of the season and the Toronto Maple Leafs beat the Montreal Canadiens 3-2 on Saturday night.

title: Giakoumakis hat trick highlights Atlanta's 4-1 victory over New England in MLS
description: Giorgos Giakoumakis scored three goals in a 19-minute stretch of the second half and Atlanta United routed the New England Revolution 4-1 in the MLS home opener for the Five Stripes.

title: No. 2 UConn overcomes 15-2 deficit to beat Providence 74-60 and likely seal No. 1 NCAA seed
description: Alex Karaban scored 16 points and Tristen Newton had 12 points, eight rebounds and five assists as second-ranked UConn bounced back after falling behind 15-2 early to beat Providence 74-60 in their regular-season finale.

title: Milling's 24 lead UC Davis over Long Beach State 88-78
description: Led by Kane Milling's 24 points, the UC Davis Aggies defeated the Long Beach State Beach 88-78 on Saturday night.

title: Southern Utah defeats UT Rio Grande Valley 68-59
description: Led by Jamari Sibley's 15 points, the Southern Utah Thunderbirds defeated the UT Rio Grande Valley Vaqueros 68-59.

title: Hlongwane's stoppage-time goal rallies Minnesota over Orlando 3-2
description: Bongokuhle Hlongwane scored in the fifth minute of second-half stoppage time and Minnesota United rallied for a wild 3-2 victory over Orlando City.

title: Forsberg has goal and an assist in debut, NY Red Bulls beat FC Dallas 2-1 in home opener
description: Emil Forsberg scored a goal and assisted on Lewis Morgan’s game-winner in his home debut for the New York Red Bulls, sparking his new club to a 2-1 victory over FC Dallas on a very wet night.

title: Union and Sounders postponed due to soggy field
description: The Philadelphia Union and Seattle Sounders game was postponed. The cross-conference game at Subaru Park was paused in the 6th minute due to a waterlogged field amid torrential storms.

title: Flyers coach John Tortorella tossed early in 7-0 loss to Lightning
description: Defenseman Darren Raddysh had five assists and the Tampa Bay Lightning beat Philadelphia 7-0 on Saturday night in a game that saw irate Flyers coach John Tortorella reluctantly leave the bench after he was ejected in the first period.

title: 5 of her kids were abducted from a Nigerian school. All she has left is hope and prayers
description: Rashidat Hamza is in despair. All but one of her six children are among the nearly 300 students abducted from their school in Nigeria’s conflict-battered northwest.

title: Dante's 19 points, 12 rebounds leads Oregon over Utah 66-65
description: N’Faly Dante scored 19 points and grabbed 12 rebounds to help Oregon beat Utah 66-65. Gabe Madsen’s 3-pointer pulled Utah to 66-63 with 3:49 remaining, and Deivon Smith’s two free throws capped the scoring with 38 seconds left.

title: Bordeleau scores twice, Chrona earns first win in net, Sharks beat Senators 2-1
description: Thomas Bordeleau scored two power-play goals, Magnus Chrona made 31 saves for his first NHL win and the San Jose Sharks beat the Ottawa Senators 2-1 to snap a nine-game losing streak.

title: Doncic is 1st in NBA to record 6 straight 30-point triple-doubles as Mavericks beat Pistons
description: DETROIT (AP) — Luka Doncic became the first NBA player to record six consecutive 30-point triple-doubles as the Dallas Mavericks pulled away in the second half and beat the Detroit Pistons 142-124 on Saturday night.

title: Capitals beat the Blackhawks 4-1 for another win that keeps them in the playoff race
description: The Washington Capitals beat the Chicago Blackhawks 4-1 for another win that keeps them very much in the Eastern Conference playoff race.

title: Johnson, Reese lead No. 8 LSU into SEC Tournament finals in a 75-67 victory over Mississippi
description: Flau'jae Johnson scored 21 points and Angel Reese had 21 points and 17 rebounds as No. 8 LSU advanced to its first SEC Tournament championship game since 2012 with a 75-67 win over Mississippi on Saturday.

title: Luka Doncic is first NBA player to have 6 straight 30-point triple-doubles as Mavericks top Pistons
description: Luka Doncic became the first NBA player to record six consecutive 30-point triple-doubles as the Dallas Mavericks pulled away in the second half and beat the Detroit Pistons 142-124.

title: Maly scores 23, Jensen 22; No. 21 Creighton beats Seton Hall in Big East quarters
description: Morgan Maly scored 23 points and grabbed nine rebounds, Lauren Jensen scored nine of her 22 points in the fourth quarter and No. 21 Creighton beat Seton Hall 72-65 in the quarterfinals of the Big East Tournament.

title: Wyoming earns 86-47 victory over Fresno State
description: Led by Akuel Kot's 17 points, the Wyoming Cowboys defeated the Fresno State Bulldogs 86-47 on Saturday night.

title: Miles Bridges scores 24, Hornets beat Nets 110-99 to snap 6-game losing streak
description: Miles Bridges had 24 points and 10 rebounds, Brandon Miller added 23 points and the Charlotte Hornets delivered another blow to the Brooklyn Nets’ sagging playoff hopes with a 110-99 win on Saturday night.

title: Noll scores 23 as Stony Brook takes down Northeastern 75-65 in CAA Tournament
description: Dean Noll scored 23 points to lead Stony Brook to a 75-65 win over Northeastern in the Coastal Athletic Association Tournament.

title: Tait-Jones scores 24 as UCSD beats Cal Poly 92-87
description: Led by Aniwaniwa Tait-Jones' 24 points, the UC San Diego Tritons defeated the Cal Poly Mustangs 92-87.

title: Appel scores 18, South Dakota State beats Oral Roberts in Summit League Tournament 79-63
description: Led by Luke Appel's 18 points, the South Dakota State Jackrabbits defeated the Oral Roberts Golden Eagles 79-63 in the Summit League Tournament.

title: LSU guard Poa taken off court on stretcher after getting hurt during SEC Tournament semifinal
description: LSU point guard Last-Tear Poa was taken off the court on a stretcher with her neck in a brace after a hard fall behind the basket late in the Tigers game with Mississippi at the Southeastern Conference Tournament on Saturday night.

title: No recoverable oil is left in the water from sheen off Southern California coast, officials say
description: Officials say no recoverable oil remains in the water after a sheen was reported off the Southern California coast, but the cause remains unclear.

title: Antwi-Boasiako scores 30, Stephen F. Austin tops Utah Tech 84-71
description: Nana Antwi-Boasiako scored 30 points to lead Stephen F. Austin to an 84-71 victory over Utah Tech.

title: Johnson scores career-high 33 points, UCF holds off TCU 79-77
description: Darius Johnson scored a career-high 33 points and UCF held off TCU for a 79-77 victory on Saturday night.

title: Harris, McGlockton help Boston College hold off Louisville 67-61
description: Claudell Harris Jr. scored 18 points and he and Devin McGlockton led a key second-half run in Boston College’s 67-61 victory over Louisville.

title: Warriors' Curry, Spurs' Wembanyama out for San Antonio-Golden State game with right ankle injuries
description: Golden State star Stephen Curry and Spurs rookie Victor Wembanyama were both out of Saturday night’s Spurs-Warriors game because of right ankle sprains.

title: Dyson scores 26 as Bethune-Cookman knocks off Florida A&M 67-66 in OT
description: Led by Dhashon Dyson's 26 points, the Bethune-Cookman Wildcats defeated the Florida A&M Rattlers 67-66 in overtime on Saturday night.

title: Leach, Goodine guide Fairfield past Mount St. Mary's 96-92
description: Jalen Leach had 29 points, Brycen Goodine scored 25 and Fairfield held off Mount St. Mary's 96-92.

title: Chandler Smith wins second career Xfinity Series race after Justin Allgaier's late flat tire
description: Chandler Smith won his second career Xfinity Series race on Saturday at Phoenix Raceway, earning a surprise victory for Toyota and Joe Gibbs Racing after leader Justin Allgaier crashed with just four laps remaining.

title: Alcorn State beats Arkansas-Pine Bluff 104-95 for ninth straight win
description: Jeremiah Gambrell had 28 points, Byron Joshua scored 20 and Alcorn State beat Arkansas-Pine Bluff 104-95 for its ninth straight victory.

title: Kam Jones scores 30, No. 8 Marquette snaps skid with 86-80 win over Xavier
description: Kam Jones had 30 points and Oso Ighodaro scored 24 to help No. 8 Marquette snap a two-game losing streak with an 86-80 victory over Xavier.

title: Colorado dumps Oregon State 73-57 behind Lampkin Jr. to close Pac-12 with six straight wins
description: Eddie Lampkin Jr. scored 17 points on 8-for-10 shooting and grabbed 11 rebounds and Colorado beat Oregon State 73-57 on Saturday to end the regular season for both teams.

title: Stevens scores 29, Colorado State downs Air Force 82-73
description: Isaiah Stevens scored 29 points as the Colorado State Rams defeated the Air Force Falcons 82-73

title: Lawrence's late layup lifts Vanderbilt past Florida, 79-78 in finale
description: Tyrin Lawrence got to the basket for a layup with 15 seconds left and Ven-Allen Lubin sealed a 79-78 upset of Florida with a last-second steal in the regular-season finale.

title: Ravindra is on 63 as New Zealand leads Australia by 149 on 3rd day of 2nd cricket test
description: Rachin Ravindra has completed his second half century in tests as New Zealand led Australia by 149 runs with seven second-innings wickets in hand at lunch on the third day of the second test.

title: Cardoso's 3-pointer at the buzzer keeps No. 1 South Carolina perfect with win over Tennessee
description: GREENVILLE, S.C. (AP) — Kamilla Cardoso banked in her first-ever 3-pointer at the buzzer and rescued No. 1 South Carolina’s perfect season with a 74-73 victory over Tennessee at the Southeastern Conference Tournament semifinals on Saturday.

title: Cook's 26 help New Mexico State defeat Florida International 77-70
description: Led by Christian Cook's 26 points, the New Mexico State Aggies defeated the Florida International Panthers 77-70 on Saturday night.

title: Toolson helps Utah Valley defeat Abilene Christian 74-67
description: Tanner Toolson had 17 points to lead Utah Valley to a 74-67 victory over Abilene Christian.
